EFG-Hermes Holding and GB Auto: Egyptian Equity Preview

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-07-12T07:47:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/efg-hermes-holding-and-gb-auto-egyptian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in  Egypt ’s stock market. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close.  The benchmark EGX30 Index dropped 2.9 percent to 5,116.21
in Cairo.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO EY): Egypt’s biggest publicly
traded investment bank, said it was the sole sell-side adviser
to Paradise Capital on the sale of its 52 percent stake in
Olympic Group for Financial Investments to  Sweden ’s  Electrolux
AB. (ELUXB)  The shares fell 0.8 percent to 20.21 Egyptian pounds.  GB Auto (AUTO EY): The biggest independent car assembler in
the  Middle East  said second-quarter passenger-car sales were
10,868 vehicles, 72 percent above the first quarter and 16
percent below the second quarter of 2010. The shares gained 0.6
percent to 30.78 pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
